The publicly available source code can be acquired from the CORAL-2 benchmarks site here:
    https://asc.llnl.gov/coral-2-benchmarks/supplementary-material.php

If using newer versions of the cuda toolkit (10+), some updates may be required.  Most notably:
    - Change env setup to match local toolkit version
    - src/halo_finder/cudaUtil.h
        ○ Change shfl_down primitives to shfl_down_sync
            § From: __shfl_down(val,*,warpSize);
            § To: __shfl_down_sync(0xFFFFFFFF, val,*,warpSize);

If issues are encountered with the defined VMAX ALIGNY size when running on multiple accelerators
it may need to be increased.

If running using MPIRun src/halo_finder/cudaUtil.h will require updates to handle MPI_LOCALRANK.  Specifically
update the cudaDeviceSelector function with:

    + else if((str = getenv("MPI_LOCALRANKID")) != NULL) {
    +     local_rank = atoi(str);
    + }
      //get the number of devices to use
      if((str = getenv("HACC_NUM_CUDA_DEV")) != NULL) {
          numDev=atoi(str);
      }

Either Intel® Math Kernel Library (MKL) or FFTW3 may be used.
